。\n警官诬陷那些他们“知道”犯了罪的嫌疑人是根本没有任何法律依据的。\n相关词组\nfit in\xa0\xa0\xa0\nfit into\xa0\xa0\xa0\nfit out\xa0\xa0\xa0\nfit up\xa0\xa0\xa0\n健康的'], ['ADJ-GRADED\nSomeone who is fit is healthy and physically strong.\nAn averagely fit person can master easy ski runs within a few days.\nC\nUNCONTROLLABLE MOVEMENTS OR EMOTIONS', '健康的;强健的\n健康的普通人几天内就可以掌握简单的滑雪技术。\n无法控制的行动或情感'], ['N-COUNT\nIf someone has a fit they suddenly lose consciousness and their body makes uncontrollable movements.\nAbout two in every five epileptic fits occur during sleep...\nOnce a fit has started there is nothing you can do to stop it.', '痉挛;昏厥\n每5例癫痫病中约有两例是在睡眠过程中发作的。\n痉挛一旦发作就无法止住。'], ['N-COUNT\nIf you have a fit of coughing or laughter, you suddenly start coughing or laughing in an uncontrollable way.\nHalfway down the cigarette she had a fit of coughing...\nIt was so unreal that I broke into a fit of giggles.', '(突然止不住的)一阵(咳嗽、大笑)\n烟抽到一半，她突然一阵猛咳。\n这实在很离奇,我忍不住咯咯笑了起来。'], ['N-COUNT\nIf you do something in a fit of anger or panic, you are very angry or afraid when you do it.\nPattie shot Tom in a fit of jealous rage.', '(愤怒、惊慌等的)爆发，发作\n帕蒂妒火中烧，开枪击中了汤姆。'], ["PHRASE\nIf you say that someone will have a fit when they hear about something, you mean that they will be very angry or shocked.\nWill Mrs Winterton have a fit if we add one more to the guest list at this late stage?...\nHe'd have a fit if he knew what we were up to!", '大发雷霆;大光其火;大吃一惊\n到这么晚的时候我们再增加一个客人，温特顿太太会发火吗？\n要是他知道我们在干什么会气疯了的。'], ['PHRASE\nSomeone who is in fits is laughing uncontrollably.\nHe was a much more entertaining person, who used to have us all in fits.', '忍不住大笑;忍俊不禁\n他以前更为风趣，常常让我们大家都捧腹大笑。'], ['PHRASE\nSomething that happens in fits and starts or by fits and starts keeps happening and then stopping again.\nMy slimming attempts tend to go in fits and starts...\nMilitary technology advances by fits and starts.', '间歇性地;一阵一阵地\n我的瘦身运动总是三天打鱼两天晒网。\n军事技术总是间断性地进步着。']]}]